6.3.2 Phase 3 deliverables
1. Phase 3 report:
o Fabrication details (filament type, printer, settings, number of reprints)
o Assembly procedure and challenges
o Test procedures, results, and interpretation
o Comparison with Phase 2 predictions (where applicable)
o Detailed discussion of failures, mistakes, and surprises
o Concrete list of design changes you would implement in a second iteration
2. Phase 3 video: Prototype Demo & Reflection
o Show the physical prototype operating.
o Demonstrate at least one test.
o Discuss major issues encountered and key lessons learned.
3. Final poster and poster session
o Create an ASU-branded poster summarizing Phases 1–3.
o Present your work during the scheduled poster session. All team members are
expected to attend and participate.
